# Recallio — Supabase + Hindsight Integration Plan

## Goal Description
Recallio requires a dual-storage approach:
1. **Supabase (PostgreSQL)**: For structured, relational data (users, subjects, chapters, test scores, scheduled tasks).
2. **Hindsight Cloud**: For agentic memory (patterns, preferences, qualitative insights, cross-session context).

This plan outlines the database schema, the role of each service, and how they synchronize to provide a personalized AI tutoring experience.

## Proposed Architecture

### Supabase Database Schema

#### 1. `users`
| Column | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | uuid (PK) | Unique user ID |
| `name` | text | User's display name |
| `onboarding_completed` | boolean | Tracks onboarding state |
| `created_at` | timestamp | |

#### 2. `subjects`
| Column | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | uuid (PK) | |
| `user_id` | uuid (FK) | Reference to `users.id` |
| `name` | text | Subject name (e.g., "Data Structures") |
| `chapters_count` | int | Total chapters in the syllabus |

#### 3. `chapters`
| Column | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | uuid (PK) | |
| `subject_id` | uuid (FK) | Reference to `subjects.id` |
| `name` | text | Chapter name |
| `order` | int | Sort order |

#### 4. `test_results`
| Column | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | uuid (PK) | |
| `user_id` | uuid (FK) | |
| `subject_id` | uuid (FK) | |
| `score` | int | Correct answers count |
| `total_questions` | int | |
| `details` | jsonb | Full Q&A mapping |
| `created_at` | timestamp | |

#### 5. `tasks` (Scheduler)
| Column | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | uuid (PK) | |
| `user_id` | uuid (FK) | |
| `title` | text | Task name |
| `date` | date | Scheduled date |
| `status` | text | 'pending', 'completed', 'rescheduled' |
| `type` | text | 'lesson', 'quiz', 'revision' |

